Question: How would you invite your friends to a party if phones and the Internet did not exist?
Answer:
As people living in the past did, there are ways to invite my friends to a party even without phones and the Internet. The most direct way is to invite them face to face and then ask them to spread the words. Or I can hire a messenger to do the invitation specifically.  If I plan well ahead of time, I can write to inform them individually. Furthermore, publicize the party on newspaper is another option available.